    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The Northern Pacific appears to\nfind it more profitable or con-\ngenial to confess judgment and\npay fines for violating law than to\ntake steps to comply with the law.\nYesterday, through its local attor-\nney in the federal court, the COM\npany admitted guilt in violating\nthe regulations designed to insure\nhumane shipment OF stock. The\ntotal fine for the offenses charged\nby the government amounted to\n$4,000.\n\n\nNot long ago the same company\nadmitted violations of the safety\nappliance law passed to protect the\nlives and limbs of trainmen, and\npaid a $1,000 fine for that."
    }
  ]
